This paper deals with the study of information overload and its impact on social media users. It involves modeling social media users as information processing systems, which falls under the category of social media analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of information overload on social contagions, which can be categorized under the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SD), social and behavioral sciences (cs.SOC), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
